  "summary": "Proof-of-concept package executes shell command at install time via postinstall hook",
  "details": "package.json declares a postinstall lifecycle script that runs an arbitrary shell command on `npm install`, writing the marker string 'PWNED_BY_DEEPLINK' to /tmp/pwned.txt on the installer's machine. The package name and payload string self-identify the artifact as a proof-of-concept demonstrating arbitrary code execution against installers. Although the current payload is a benign marker write rather than exfiltration or persistence, the package's stated and demonstrated purpose is to execute attacker-author-supplied shell commands on every machine that installs it, with no legitimate functionality offered in exchange.",
